
Boating and logistics
Leading the sailing programme and on-water logistics Jamie is demonstrating he hasn’t progressed that far since school and university as head of boats and social sec. The schedule promises to be broad though; organising which toys to use on which days will be no mean feat with paddle boarding, kitesurfing, dinghy sailing, body surfing, beach cricket, snorkelling and diving amongst the available kit to choose from. Now, where can we find a cheap wingfoil setup from?

Engineering
Jamie also takes on most things engineering-related, keeping the boat’s mechanical and electronic systems running, including communications both close to port and at sea. This in itself is a full time job and relies on dragging engineering knowledge learned at university 25 years ago into the real world (or more realistically, from YouTube!).

“This will be easy, it’s going to be downwind warm weather sailing”

– Jamie Reid (some months before setting out from Northern France in mid-November, reefed down into a strong headwind, wearing pretty much every item of clothing we’d each brought onto the boat)